                      "part": null,
                      "issue": null,
                      "page": "1458"
                    },
                    "date": 1953
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "the double-chamber fission counting apparatus."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USABNL"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USABNL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Brookhaven pile."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "2x10**11 n/cm**2/sec, the flux was constant to +- 2%",
                "after reaching its full value."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC",
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two gas proportional counters with",
                "silver cathodes, 2 cm dia. and 30 cm long. The",
                "krypton pressure was about 300 mm and methane was",
                "added to bring the total pressure to 1 atm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The fission foils, which consist of 0.01 microg of",
                "235U or 239Pu deposited on a Pt disk 0.002 inch thick",
                "and 1 inch in diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "FISCT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Absolute radiochemical methods, fission",
                "yields to half life (Y/T). Foils were mounted on",
                "platinum in each of the two chambers of fission",
                "counting apparatus. The entire assembly was then",
                "irradiated in the brookhaven graphite reactor for",
                "6-12 hr, and the fission counting rates of the foils",
                "were recorded continuously. After irradiation the",
                "85Kr was radiochemically separated from the slug,",
                "purified, and its activity measured by internal gas",
                "phase proportional counting. From these values of the",
                "85Kr activity and the measured number of fissions the",
                "fission yield was calculated."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
